news.title: Chandigarh: Ongoing VB probe casts shadow on Manimajra housing project
news.para: Chandigarh's Municipal Corporation faces scrutiny over a high-value housing project in Manimajra due to the absence of a formal policy for allocating 15% of units to the Economically Weaker Section, as mandated. This comes amid a Vigilance investigation into the Uppal Housing Society's failure to construct EWS houses.

news.title: Nagpur civic body to soon launch housing project for sanitation workers
news.para: The Nagpur Municipal Corporation is set to launch a housing project under the Dr. Babasaheb Ambedkar Awas Yojana, constructing 392 flats for sanitation workers. A cashless health insurance scheme offering coverage up to Rs10 lakh will also be rolled out.

news.title: Chandigarh: Drone survey done, field verification to begin on September 20
news.para: The Chandigarh administration's NAKSHA pilot program has completed its drone survey, with field verification of property features set to begin on September 20. Twenty survey teams have been formed to systematically conduct the exercise across five villages and fifteen sectors. Deputy Commissioner Nishant Kumar Yadav emphasized the importance of surveyor training and adherence to project timelines during a review meeting.

news.title: Major push to attract GCCs, Andhra Pradesh constitutes a 360-degree advisory council
news.para: Andhra Pradesh is aggressively pursuing Global Capability Centres (GCCs) to become a major digital economy hub. The state government has formed a 360-degree GCC advisory council, led by Nara Lokesh, to attract investments and create a strategic roadmap. This initiative aims to foster innovation, develop infrastructure, and create a future-ready talent pool through collaborations and global outreach.

news.title: Embassy REIT rejects Sterling Wilson’s ₹100-crore claim, cites tribunal rulings
news.para: Embassy Office Parks REIT has refuted Sterling Wilson's claims of a Rs 100-crore payment due from Embassy Energy Pvt Ltd, terming them as baseless and previously dismissed by judicial forums. The dispute dates back to 2018, before EEPL became part of the REIT. Embassy REIT asserts it has fulfilled all obligations and will contest Sterling Wilson's attempts to exert pressure.

news.title: Amazon leases 2.2 lakh sq ft office space in Chennai
news.para: Amazon Development Centre India has leased 220,000 sq ft from WeWork in Chennai, marking the largest office transaction in the city this year. The 40-month lease will accommodate over 3,500 work units, highlighting Amazon's expansion in southern India and the growing demand for flexible workspaces. This deal positions Chennai as a key real estate market alongside Bengaluru and Hyderabad.

news.title: Maharashtra cabinet clears plan to borrow ₹2,000 crore from Hudco for urban infra projects
news.para: The Maharashtra state cabinet has approved a Rs 2,000 crore loan from HUDCO to fund urban infrastructure projects across various municipal corporations, including water supply and sewage initiatives in Chhatrapati Sambhajinagar, Nagpur, and Mira Bhayandar.

news.title: Mumbai: Illegal building demolition halted in Dombivli as urban development department summons KDMC chief
news.para: A planned demolition of Samarth Complex, an illegal building in Kalyan-Dombivli, was halted after residents protested with threats of self-immolation. The action was paused as the state urban development department intervened. Residents claim they were misled by fake RERA certificates and assurances from the government against demolitions, leaving their future uncertain.

news.title: Fraudulent misuse of insolvency law, NCLAT rules in Logix Infrastructure case
news.para: The NCLAT has dismissed bankruptcy proceedings against Logix Infrastructure, citing fraudulent misuse of insolvency law. The appellate tribunal found Experts Realty Professionals (ERP) and Logix were related parties colluding to shield Logix from liabilities. ERP faces penalties for concealing this relationship and attempting to manipulate the insolvency process, as the tribunal highlighted suspect financial transactions and director overlaps.

news.title: Godrej Interio to invest ₹300 crore; aims to double revenues to ₹10,000 crore by FY29
news.para: Godrej Interio plans a Rs 300 crore investment in business expansion and technology to double its revenue to Rs 10,000 crore by FY29. The company aims to increase its market share in the organized furniture sector to over 20%. This investment includes digital technologies, store expansion to 1,500 outlets, and design enhancements, shifting the revenue focus towards B2C growth.

news.title: Godrej preparing masterplan to develop 1,000 acres of Vikhroli land
news.para: The Godrej Enterprise Group is developing a masterplan for its expansive 1,000-acre Vikhroli property in Mumbai. Executive Director Nyrika Holkar confirmed ongoing manufacturing activities alongside future systematic development. While some land is leased to IT firms, Godrej & Boyce businesses remain.

news.title: ED attaches fresh ₹186 crore assets in bank fraud case against DHFL
news.para: The Enforcement Directorate has attached assets worth approximately Rs 186 crore in the Dewan Housing Finance Corporation Limited (DHFL) loan fraud case. The attached assets include flats and receivables in Mumbai. The ED's action follows a CBI FIR against DHFL, Kapil Wadhawan, and Dheeraj Wadhawan. They are accused of siphoning off bank loan funds.

news.title: USA: Shortage of homebuyers forces many sellers to lower prices or walk away as sales slump drags on
news.para: Across the U.S., sellers are finding it harder to command top dollar as affordability challenges and new construction give buyers more leverage. Increased inventory, particularly in the South and West, is prompting price reductions and concessions. While national listing prices saw a slight rise in July, several metro areas experienced declines, signaling a shift in the housing market dynamic.

news.title: Sebi amends InvITs rules; cuts min investment threshold
news.para: SEBI has eased norms for InvITs and REITs, reducing the minimum allotment lot size for privately placed InvITs to ₹25 lakh, aligning it with secondary market norms. The regulator has also relaxed rules regarding related parties and cash flow distribution for holding companies.

news.title: Glass Wall Systems files draft papers with Sebi to raise funds via IPO
news.para: Glass Wall Systems (India) Ltd has filed papers with Sebi for an IPO, planning to raise funds through a fresh issue of shares worth Rs 60 crore and an OFS of 4.02 crore shares. The proceeds will be used for a GPU project and general corporate purposes.

news.title: Indore metro’s underground run may extend till Khajrana square
news.para: The Madhya Pradesh Legislative Assembly's Estimates Committee has proposed extending Indore Metro's underground track by 2 km, stretching from Airport to Khajrana Square. This extension aims to resolve land acquisition issues and facilitate station construction. While praising urban development, the Public Accounts Committee criticized incomplete drainage lines and poor road conditions, urging better monitoring and penalties for contractors.

news.title: NBCC inks pact with NMRDA to build Naveen Nagpur
news.para: NBCC (India) and NMRDA have partnered to develop Naveen Nagpur, an International Business & Finance Center (IBFC) spanning 1,710 acres. NBCC will act as the project management consultant for the 1,000-acre business district, focusing on commercial establishments, residential areas, and mixed-use developments. The project will be executed in three phases over 15 years.

news.title: ED raids 27 locations across West Bengal in connection with illegal sand mining
news.para: The Enforcement Directorate (ED) conducted extensive raids across 27 locations in West Bengal targeting illegal sand mining operations. These searches focused on a major sand-mining company with operations spanning multiple states, including Bengal, and its directors.

news.title: Sundaram Home enters Karnataka; eyes ₹60 crore disbursements under EB segment
news.para: Sundaram Home Finance is expanding into Karnataka, targeting Tier II and III towns with 8-10 new branches. The company aims to disburse Rs 60 crore in the first year, focusing on small business loans and affordable housing finance. This move is driven by the potential in Karnataka's affordable housing segment, supported by government initiatives.

news.title: Flipspaces secures $50 million in series C round
news.para: Flipspaces secured USD 50 million in its expanded Series C funding, drawing investments from CE-Invests, Panthera Growth Partners, and SMBC Asia Rising Fund. This funding will fuel expansion in India, the U.S., and the U.A.E., alongside supply chain improvements and AI-driven technology enhancements. The round also facilitated the exit of early investor Carpe Diem.
